<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-12880] Atom consumer stops polling</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-12880</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Camel-atom consumer stops polling for new feeds when a connection error occurs. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It uses java.net.HttpURLConnection without a connection timeout value(The default value is 0 i.e. no timeout).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When network error occur, connection threads hang and it causes ScheduledExecutorService stop polling.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
